---
description: Vibe Paper rule for project-root paper writing
globs:
  - "paper/**/*.tex"
  - "paper/**/*.bib"
  - "paper/context/project_snapshot.md"
alwaysApply: false
---

This project uses Vibe Paper.

Read `paper/context/project_snapshot.md` before drafting or editing the paper.

Treat the whole project root as readable context. Treat `paper/` as the writable paper workspace.

Preserve numeric claims from real code, logs, configs, and exported result files. Do not invent missing metrics, baselines, or dataset counts.

When compilation is needed, use the local Vibe Paper build flow instead of editor-specific LaTeX commands. If the user wants preview, prefer the native popup script entrypoint over editor-integrated preview.
